  "text": "Recombinant active human PAI-1 (2.5 μg; American Diagnostica) and human plasma Vn (5 μg; Promega) were incubated for 1 h at 37°C in a volume of 5 μl to form a complex [CITATION_1] . Bacteria (20 μl, 4 × 10 7 cells) in PBS were incubated with the complex for 2 h at 37°C. The bacteria were pelleted, and the supernatants were run in a 12% (wt/vol) SDS-PAGE gel, and PAI-1 and Vn were detected by Western blotting with polyclonal anti-PAI-1 (1:5000, Calbiochem) or anti-Vn (1:1000, Calbiochem) antibodies, alkaline-phosphataseconjugated anti-rabbit immunoglobulin G (Dako) and phosphatase substrate.",
